ted sarandos  wikipedia ted sarandos from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search ted sarandos born theodore anthony sarandos jr  july   age  phoenix arizona us residence los angeles california us nationality american education glendale community college occupation businessman employer netflix salary us million title chief content officer political party democratic spouses michelle sarandos div nicole avant present children  parents theodore sarandos sr relatives clarence avant fatherinlaw theodore ted anthony sarandos jr born july   is an american businessman of greek heritage he is the chief content officer for netflix sarandos oversees netflixs  revenue of us billion and  operating income of us million and with his guidance the company received   primetime emmy awards contents  early life  career  honors  board and advisory work  philanthropy  personal life  references  external links early lifeedit sarandos was born in phoenix arizona to father ted sarandos who was an electrician and a mother who was a stayathome mom he is the fourth of five children with three older sisters and a younger brother sarandos paternal grandfather came from the greek island of samos to the united states as a young boy his family name was originally kiriazakis but he changed it to sarandos while in high school writing for his high school newspaper sarandos met and interviewed the actor ed asner who was in phoenix for a local screen actors guild meeting asner then in the height of his lou grant period ended up introducing him to others in the entertainment industry for further interviews and connected his interests in entertainment politics and journalism sarandos attended glendale community college in glendale arizona he also attended arizona state university where he was a journalism major until he left college to manage the video store where he worked since high school arizona video cassettes west careeredit from  to  sarandos managed eight retail video stores in the arizona video cassettes west chain in  sarandos became western regional director of sales and operations for one of the largest video distributors in the united states east texas distributors etd until march  sarandos was vice president of product and merchandising for the almost  store chain video citywest coast video while at west coast video he was responsible for negotiating revenue deals to migrate from the company from the vhs format into the dvd format after meeting netflix ceo reed hastings in  sarandos joined netflix in  he serves as its chief content officer sarandos was responsible for initiating the first round of original programming at netflix starting with lilyhammer and then continuing with the breakout david fincher series starring kevin spacey house of cards beginning with house of cards which was bought for  million in a march  deal sarandos created the model where netflix purchases multiple seasons of shows without pilot orders sarandos sees the focus as being on subscriber growth as a reflection of revenue health over ratings especially because the adsupported model doesnt apply to netflix sarandos uses algorithms at netflix to predict what programs viewers will want to watch prior to producing them his personal algorithm focuses on  judgement as a highest priority with  focused on a base of data he also said that the focus is on the audience and that there is no programming grid – or appointment linearbased television – that is typically used by traditional tv networks barometers of success are if the audience completes watching the show the timeframe within which they finish watching a show if there is social media buzz by critics and fans sarandos said that the preference is for show to run for multiple seasons and build a fan base sarandos says the model allows the viewer to be in control and to watch only the content they enjoy the more serialized the show is the longer the revenue stream sarandos sees cost per hour basis as greater the more total run time there is across the lifetime of a show as it is often not a cost savings to produce less original content once production is underway sarandos said the comparison of tv network ratings to netflix isnt meaningful as the typical netflix release model of pushing out content is full season availability at once no advertising means theres no need for typical ratings he said netflix aggregates audiences over a very long period of time where netflix can tell if a show will be successful by using a regression models that tells netflix based on first hour of viewing how successful the show will be over the life of its license sarandos has been outspoken about discarding or not holding important traditional network models of which although historically a big tv fan he describes the model as now becoming archaic sarandos sees the new model as a way to prioritize the needs and desires of the consumer part of this is the refusal to release ratings and metrics of viewership international reach and long tail niche appeal is also an important part of the business model the spend is typically a large upfront payment with no backend fees to talent and creators especially of original content that netflix owns sarandos said that he sees the netflix brand as being based on personalization that it was a deliberate choice on the part of netflix to focus on providing diverse content that would appeal to the tastes of a broad base of viewers one that would not be focused on a marquee show that netflix would be known for but quality shows that would appeal to different audiences sarandos sees netflix as a digital product where the balance between distributing physical bits of content versus streaming digital content would be cheaper as both broadband and netflix grew ie postal economics vs streaming economics this was something that sarandos said he and his team was closely analyzing at a micro fiscal level the shift away from the dvd business comes from this evaluation of new model focused on streaming and includes original programming which is one of the main responsibilities of sarandos work at netflix sarandos set up a multipicture deal with adam sandler which was met with criticism in defense sarandos said that the numbers make sense something he characterizes as datainfluenced intuition and that sandler has a global appeal sarandos characterized sandlers  film the ridiculous  as successful saying it garnered the highest number of netflix viewers streaming a film within the first  days of its release during the  television critics association presentation sarandos said he expects the amount netflix spends on original programming to rise considerably and in terms of volume for  sarandos said that netflix will be showing over  hours of original programming honorsedit  aspen institute – henry crown fellow  the hollywood reporter – digital power   the hollywood reporter – “digital power ”  time – time   simon wiesenthal center – humanitarian award  international documentary association – pioneer award  the hollywood reporter – silicon beach power   napte – brandon tartikoff legacy award variety – “global ”citation needed the hollywood reporter – “indie power ”citation needed board and advisory workedit sarandos is a member of many boards academy of television arts  sciences executive committee appointee  member digital entertainment group retail advisory boardcitation needed exploring the arts board of trustees international documentary association trustee los angeles greek film festival advisory board los angeles film festival film independent film advisory board mediarightsorg board of directorscitation needed tribeca film festival film advisory boardcitation needed video software dealers association former chapter president  board membercitation needed philanthropyedit sarandos and his wife avant a key fundraiser for obama in southern california in  raised us for democratic candidate barack obamas  campaign personal lifeedit sarandos married michelle sarandos his first wife with whom he had two children sarah and tony in  sarandos married former united states ambassador to the bahamas  nicole avant the daughter of former motown chairman clarence avant producer lawrence bender introduced sarandos to avant sarandos and his wife live in the hancock park neighborhood of los angeles after previously living in avants home town of beverly hills california in  the couple purchased a beach house formerly owned by david spade in malibu california sarandos has said he is catholic referencesedit  the greek who has found hollywood for the internet gr reporter  december  retrieved  september    λιβέρη μάγδα  july  ο ελληνας που έφερε το χόλιγουντ στο διαδίκτυο ethnos εθνος retrieved  september    a b theodore a sarandos  united states public records familysearch  july  retrieved  september    a b papapostolou anastasios  january  ted sarandos talks netflix boom and greek heritage greek reporter retrieved  september    form  statement of changes in beneficial ownership  netflix inc reported by sarandos theodore a fy  pdf edgar  january  retrieved  september    a b c d e segal david  february  the netflix fix the new york times retrieved  september    a b belloni matthew rose lacey  august  tv titans roundtable  chiefs spar over the future and netflixs role as archfrenemy the hollywood reporter retrieved  september    a b belloni matthew rose lacey  august  thr full tv executives roundtable ft the titans behind hbo netflix amc ae  nbcuniversal video the hollywood reporter retrieved  september    a b c d e fernandez giselle  december  big shots full conversation with ted sarandos video interview los angeles retrieved  september    bland karina  may  what ms fiedler taught me about telling stories the arizona republic retrieved  september    a b martinson jane  march  netflix’s ted sarandos ‘we like giving great storytellers big canvases’ the guardian retrieved  february    a b daunt tina  april  obamas  po