resident chief executive officer of netflix inc mr hastings founded pure software which made tools for software developers after a  ipo and several acquisitions pure was acquired by rational software in  mr hastings is an active educational philanthropist and served on the california state board of education from  to  he is currently on the board of several educational organizations including ccsa dreambox learning kipp and pahara mr hastings is also a board member of facebook and was on the board of microsoft from  to  mr hastings received a ba from bowdoin college in  and an mscs in artificial intelligence from stanford university in  between bowdoin and stanford mr hastings served in the peace corps as a high school math teacher in swaziland david wells mr david b wells is a chief financial officer of netflix inc mr wells has served as the companys chief financial officer since  his responsibilities include a number of operating duties such as customer service real estate and employee technology mr wells has been at netflix since march  serving in a variety of planning and analysis roles including most recently as the vice president of financial planning  analysis prior to joining netflix mr wells served in progressive roles at deloitte consulting from august  to march  and at various nonprofit organizations before getting his mba mr wells joined the board of the trade desk a public company that provides a technology platform for ad buyers in january  mr wells holds an mba and mpp from the university of chicago and a bachelors degree in commerce from the university of virginia kelly bennett mr kelly bennett is a chief marketing officer of netflix inc mr kelly bennett became netflixs chief marketing officer in  after nearly a decade at warner bros where he was most recently vice president interactive world wide marketing with the pictures group leading international online campaigns for warner bros movies before that mr bennett ran digital marketing for warner bros pictures in europe the middle east and africa and worked in promotion and business development at the company he previously held executive positions at dow jones international and ignition media as well as being a partner in online marketing agency cimex media the canadaborn bennett is a graduate of simon fraser university david hyman mr david hyman is a general counsel secretary of netflix inc mr hyman is general counsel for netflix responsible for all legal and public policy matters for the company he has served in this capacity since  and also serves as the company’s secretary prior to netflix mr hyman was the general counsel of webvan an online internet retailer having previously held the role of senior corporate counsel he also practiced law at morrison  foerster in san francisco and arent fox in washington dc mr hyman earned his jd and bachelor’s degrees from the university of virginia jonathan friedland mr jonathan s friedland is a chief communications officer of netflix inc mr jonathan friedland joined netflix in  from the walt disney company where he was svp corporate communications before that he spent over  years as a foreign correspondent and editor mainly with the wall street journal in the us asia and latin america and cofounded the diarios rumbo chain of spanishlanguage newspapers in texas mr friedland who has a msc economics from the london school of economics and a ba from hampshire college was a member of the wsj team that won the pulitzer prize for its coverage of the  attacks greg peters mr greg peters is a chief product officer of netflix inc he was chief streaming and partnerships officer of netflix inc mr peters has served as the company’s chief streaming and partnerships officer since july  from october  to july  mr peters served as vp engineering prior to joining netflix mr peters served as senior vice president of consumer electronics products for macrovision solutions corp later renamed to rovi corporation and previously held positions at digital entertainment software provider mediabolic inc red hat network the provider of linux and open source technology and online vendor winecom mr peters holds a degree in physics and astronomy from yale university theodore sarandos mr theodore a sarandos is a chief content officer of netflix inc since  mr sarandos has led content acquisition for netflix since  with more than  years experience in home entertainment mr sarandos is recognized in the industry as an innovator in film acquisition and distribution before netflix mr sarandos was an executive at video distributor etd and video city  west coast video mr sarandos is a henry crown fellow at the aspen institute and serves on the board of exploring the arts a nonprofit focused on arts in schools he also serves on the film advisory board for tribeca and los angeles film festival is an american cinematheque board member an executive committee member of the academy of television arts  sciences and is a trustee of the american film institute jay hoag mr jay c hoag is a lead independent director of netflix inc since june  he has served as a founding general partner at technology crossover ventures a venture capital firm mr hoag serves on the board of directors of electronic arts inc tech target and zillow inc and several private companies previously mr hoag served on the boards of directors of eharmony inc and thestreetcom mr hoag holds an mba from the university of michigan and a ba from northwestern university richard barton mr richard n barton is an independent director of netflix inc in late  mr barton cofounded zillow group inc where he is now executive chairman of the board additionally mr barton is a venture partner with benchmark capital previously mr barton founded expedia inc in  and was its president chief executive officer and director from november  to march  mr barton was a director of interactivecorp from february  until january  mr barton also serves as a director for avvo inc and glassdoorcom mr barton holds a bs in general engineering  industrial economics from stanford university a george battle mr a george battle is an independent director of netflix inc he was previously executive chairman of the board of ask jeeves inc which was acquired by iacinteractivecorp in july  he was chief executive officer of ask jeeves from  to  from  until his retirement in  mr battle served in management roles at arthur andersen llp and then andersen consulting llp now accenture where he became worldwide managing partner of market development and a member of the firm’s executive committee educated at dartmouth college and the stanford graduate school of business mr battle currently serves as chairman of the board of fair isaac corporation and as a director of the following public companies linkedin corporation workday inc and expedia inc he was previously a director of advent software inc opentable inc and the masters select family of mutual funds timothy haley mr timothy m haley is an independent director of netflix inc he is a cofounder of redpoint ventures a venture capital firm and has been a managing director of the firm since october  mr haley has been a managing director of institutional venture partners a venture capital firm since february  from june  to february  mr haley was the president of haley associates an executive recruiting firm in the high technology industry mr haley currently serves on the board of directors of several private companies mr haley holds a ba from santa clara university leslie kilgore ms leslie jean kilgore is an independent director of netflix inc since  ms kilgore has been a director of linkedin corporation and serves as chair on its compensation committee ms kilgore served as the company’s chief marketing officer formerly vice president of marketing from  until her resignation in february  from february  to march  ms kilgore served as director of marketing for amazoncom inc an internet retailer ms kilgore served as a brand manager for the procter  gamble company a manufacturer and marketer of consumer products from august  to february  ms kilgore holds an mba from the stanford university graduate school of business and a bs from the wharton school of business at the university of pennsylvania ann mather ms ann mather is an independent director of netflix inc since september  he has been a director of glu mobile inc a publisher of mobile games since november  ms mather has been a director of google inc and serves as chair of its audit committee since may  ms mather has been a director of moneygram international a global payment services company and serves as chair of its audit committee on march   ms mather indicated her intention not to stand for reelection at the upcoming annual meeting of moneygram stockholders since december  ms mather has been a director of mgm holdings inc “mgm” the independent privatelyheld motion picture television home video and theatrical production and distribution company since april  ms mather has been a director of solazyme inc a renewable oil and bioproducts company and serves as chair of its audit committee ms mather has also been an independent trustee to the dodge  cox funds board of trustees since may  ms mather was chair of shoppingcom’s audit committee and a member of its corporate governance and nominating committee from  to  she was executive vice president and chief financial officer of pixar a computer animation studio prior to her service at pixar ms mather was executive vice president and chief financial officer at village roadshow pictures the film production division of village roadshow limited from  to  she held various executive positions at the walt disney company including senior vice president of finance and administration for its buena vista international theatrical division ms mather holds a master of arts degree from cambridge university bradford smith mr bradford lee smith is an independent director of the netflix inc mr smith has been with microsoft since  and became the general counsel and executive vice president of legal and corporate affairs in  and currently serves as the president and chief legal officer prior to joining microsoft he was an associate and then partner at the washington dcbased firm of covington and burling mr smith holds a ba in international relations and economics from princeton university and a jd from columbia university school of law he also studied international law and economics at the graduate institute of international studies in geneva anne sweeney ms anne m sweeney is an independent director of netflix inc most recently ms sweeney was cochair disney media networks and president disneyabc television group previously ms sweeney served as chairman and ceo of the fx networks part of the fox entertainment group of st century fox and spent more than  years at viacom’s nickelodeon network ms sweeney holds a ba from the college of new rochelle and an ed m from harvard university having held various senior positions with large entertainment companies ms sweeney brings broad strategic and operational experience to the board her experience in the entertainment industry provides a unique business perspective to the company as it builds its global internet tv network basic compensation name fiscal year total reed hastings  david wells  kelly bennett  david hyman  jonathan friedland  greg peters  theodore sarandos  jay hoag  richard barton  a george battle  timothy haley  leslie kilgore  ann mather  bradford smith  anne sweeney  as of   dec  options compensation name options value reed hastings   david wells   kelly bennett   david hyman   jonathan friedland   greg peters   theodore sarandos   jay hoag   richard barton   a george battle   timothy haley   leslie kilgore   ann mather   bradford smith   anne sweeney   insider trading name shares traded price hastings reed   hastings reed   hastings reed   hastings reed   sarandos theodore a jr   sarandos theodore a jr   sarandos theodore