 television – that is typically used by traditional tv networks barometers of success are if the audience completes watching the show the timeframe within which they finish watching a show if there is social media buzz by critics and fans sarandos said that the preference is for show to run for multiple seasons and build a fan base sarandos says the model allows the viewer to be in control and to watch only the content they enjoy the more serialized the show is the longer the revenue stream sarandos sees cost per hour basis as greater the more total run time there is across the lifetime of a show as it is often not a cost savings to produce less original content once production is underway sarandos said the comparison of tv network ratings to netflix isnt meaningful as the typical netflix release model of pushing out content is full season availability at once no advertising means theres no need for typical ratings he said netflix aggregates audiences over a very long period of time where netflix can tell if a show will be successful by using a regression models that tells netflix based on first hour of viewing how successful the show will be over the life of its license sarandos has been outspoken about discarding or not holding important traditional network models of which although historically a big tv fan he describes the model as now becoming archaic sarandos sees the new model as a way to prioritize the needs and desires of the consumer part of this is the refusal to release ratings and metrics of viewership international reach and long tail niche appeal is also an important part of the business model the spend is typically a large upfront payment with no backend fees to talent and creators especially of original content that netflix owns sarandos said that he sees the netflix brand as being based on personalization that it was a deliberate choice on the part of netflix to focus on providing diverse content that would appeal to the tastes of a broad base of viewers one that would not be focused on a marquee show that netflix would be known for but quality shows that would appeal to different audiences sarandos sees netflix as a digital product where the balance between distributing physical bits of content versus streaming digital content would be cheaper as both broadband and netflix grew ie postal economics vs streaming economics this was something that sarandos said he and his team was closely analyzing at a micro fiscal level the shift away from the dvd business comes from this evaluation of new model focused on streaming and includes original programming which is one of the main responsibilities of sarandos work at netflix sarandos set up a multipicture deal with adam sandler which was met with criticism in defense sarandos said that the numbers make sense something he characterizes as datainfluenced intuition and that sandler has a global appeal sarandos characterized sandlers  film the ridiculous  as successful saying it garnered the highest number of netflix viewers streaming a film within the first  days of its release during the  television critics association presentation sarandos said he expects the amount netflix spends on original programming to rise considerably and in terms of volume for  sarandos said that netflix will be showing over  hours of original programming honorsedit  aspen institute – henry crown fellow  the hollywood reporter – digital power   the hollywood reporter – “digital power ”  time – time   simon wiesenthal center – humanitarian award  international documentary association – pioneer award  the hollywood reporter – silicon beach power   napte – brandon tartikoff legacy award variety – “global ”citation needed the hollywood reporter – “indie power ”citation needed board and advisory workedit sarandos is a member of many boards academy of television arts  sciences executive committee appointee  member digital entertainment group retail advisory boardcitation needed exploring the arts board of trustees international documentary association trustee los angeles greek film festival advisory board los angeles film festival film independent film advisory board mediarightsorg board of directorscitation needed tribeca film festival film advisory boardcitation needed video software dealers association former chapter president  board membercitation needed philanthropyedit sarandos and his wife avant a key fundraiser for obama in southern california in  raised us for democratic candidate barack obamas  campaign personal lifeedit sarandos married michelle sarandos his first wife with whom he had two children sarah and tony in  sarandos married former united states ambassador to the bahamas  nicole avant the daughter of former motown chairman clarence avant producer lawrence bender introduced sarandos to avant sarandos and his wife live in the hancock park neighborhood of los angeles after previously living in avants home town of beverly hills california in  the couple purchased a beach house formerly owned by david spade in malibu california sarandos has said he is catholic referencesedit  the greek who has found hollywood for the internet gr reporter  december  retrieved  september    λιβέρη μάγδα  july  ο ελληνας που έφερε το χόλιγουντ στο διαδίκτυο ethnos εθνος retrieved  september    a b theodore a sarandos  united states public records familysearch  july  retrieved  september    a b papapostolou anastasios  january  ted sarandos talks netflix boom and greek heritage greek reporter retrieved  september    form  statement of changes in beneficial ownership  netflix inc reported by sarandos theodore a fy  pdf edgar  january  retrieved  september    a b c d e segal david  february  the netflix fix the new york times retrieved  september    a b belloni matthew rose lacey  august  tv titans roundtable  chiefs spar over the future and netflixs role as archfrenemy the hollywood reporter retrieved  september    a b belloni matthew rose lacey  august  thr full tv e